article.description: Dane Pineau scored 20 points and led four players in double digits as Saint Mary's rolled over Southern Utah 92-36 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Saint Mary's rolls over Southern Utah 92-36
article.linkText: Saint Mary's rolls over Southern Utah 92-36
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. -- Dane Pineau scored 20 points and led four players in double digits as Saint Mary's rolled over Southern Utah 92-36 on Wednesday night. Pineau did it with 10-of-12 shooting from the field for the Gaels (8-1). He also had six rebounds and six assists. Emmett Naar added 16 points, five assists and five steals and Calvin Hermanson and Franklin Porter had 15 points apiece. Pineau struck six times from inside the paint in less than five minutes early in the first half, sparking a 23-9 start for the Gaels on their way to a 47-19 lead at the break. The Gaels averaged 62.5 percent shooting from the field, 57.1 percent from the line and made 14 of 26 (53.8 percent) from beyond the arc. They also had a 39-20 rebounding edge over Southern Utah. James McGee led the Thunderbirds (3-6) with 15 points.
